  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>1.17.10 is a minor update including some small features and bug fixes.</p><p>Released 11:30 CST on July 20</p><h3 id=\"id-1.17.10-NewFeatures\">New Features</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427638/Ticket+Properties+Require+a+Ticket+Resolution\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427638\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Require a ticket resolution</a> before entering a specific ticket status.</p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427651/Ticket+Properties+Requiring+a+Ticket+Assignee\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427651\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Require a ticket assignee</a> before entering a specific ticket status.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"id-1.17.10-EnhancementsandBugFixes\">Enhancements and Bug Fixes</h3><ul><li><p>A VCT is now required when voiding a ticket so that any voided payments can be accounted for when closing the cash drawer.</p></li><li><p>Added new in-app controls to manage <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624095/RepairQ+Support+Login+Authorization\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624095\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RepairQ support team login access</a> to perform troubleshooting.</p></li><li><p>The inventory item list (for a given catalog item) will now show the location specific price for the catalog item instead of the default catalog item price.</p></li><li><p>The device list manufacturer filter will now show only the manufacturers that have repairable devices linked.</p></li><li><p>Performance optimizations that will reduce page load times.</p></li><li><p>We fixed an issue with Qsite that would limit the number of compatible services that would be listed for a device.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue with saving IP whitelist changes for a staff user.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue with including custom forms on claim tickets.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue that prevented unsetting the billing agent on the ticket.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue that would hide the \u201cquick links\u201d on the dashboard when the check-in widget was enabled.</p></li></ul>",
      "representation": "export_view",
